The paper focuses on fine-grained visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves self-supervised proposal mining and discriminative scale mining, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions feature pyramid and pooling operations, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
